# .dockerignore — trim the Docker build context (unrelated to .gitignore).
#
# The Dockerfile copies only the prebuilt binary from dist/ (the gomatic
# `make docker` pattern: build-all populates dist/ first), so the build context
# needs nothing else. Ignore everything except dist/. The Dockerfile and
# .dockerignore themselves are always available to the builder regardless.
#
# NOTE: repos whose Dockerfile instead builds from source with `COPY . .` use
# the opposite shape — exclude dist/, bin/, var/, .git, editor dirs, docs — and
# keep the sources (see e.g. modern-go-application, skyctl).
*
!dist
